# POLARIS MASTER ISSUER PROGRAMME - EXECUTIVE SUMMARY

## CURRENT SITUATION

**Polaris Track Record (2019-2025):**

- 11 completed RMBS transactions
- Accelerating cadence: 3 deals in 2025 alone
- Deal sizes: £295m-£720m
- Arrangers: BofA Securities, Citigroup
- Collateral: Non-conforming UK residential mortgages (owner-occupied + BTL)
- Structure: Each deal = separate SPV (Polaris 202X-X plc)

**2026+ Plan:**

- 5 deals per year
- £150m firsts + £40m seconds monthly origination (£1.15bn+ annual)
- Need systematic funding solution
- Call refinancing requirements for legacy deals

-----

## WHY MASTER ISSUER STRUCTURE?

### The Key Distinction

**Master Trust (e.g., Godiva) = NOT VIABLE**

- ❌ Shared collateral pool across all series
- ❌ Regulatory restrictions for specialist lenders
- ❌ Rating agency barriers for non-conforming collateral

**Master Issuer/Series Programme (e.g., Economic) = PERFECT FIT**

- ✅ Single SPV entity, discrete collateral pools per series
- ✅ No cross-collateralization
- ✅ Accepted for specialist/non-conforming lenders
- ✅ Used successfully by UK specialist lenders

-----

## ECONOMIC BUILDING SOCIETY PRECEDENT

**Why This Matters:**

- Specialist lender (near-prime, non-conforming) - **just like Polaris**
- Regional building society, not mainstream bank
- Non-STS eligible collateral
- Successfully operates “Economic Master Issuer plc”
- Multiple series issued from single platform
- Each series: discrete pool, independent rating, no cross-collateralization

**Their Structure:**

```
Economic Master Issuer plc (single SPV)
├─ Mortgage Funding Series 2017-1 (£200m) - Pool A
├─ Mortgage Funding Series 2018-1 (£250m) - Pool B  
├─ Mortgage Funding Series 2019-1 (£300m) - Pool C
├─ Mortgage Funding Series 2020-1 (£275m) - Pool D
└─ Mortgage Funding Series 2022-1 (£350m) - Pool E

One master framework, rapid series execution, massive cost savings
```

-----

## PROPOSED STRUCTURE: POLARIS MASTER ISSUER PLC

### Transformation

**FROM (Current):**

```
Polaris 2026-1 plc (new SPV) → Full docs, £2-2.5m cost
Polaris 2026-2 plc (new SPV) → Full docs, £2-2.5m cost
Polaris 2026-3 plc (new SPV) → Full docs, £2-2.5m cost
[Repeat for each deal]
```

**TO (Master Issuer):**

```
Polaris Master Issuer plc (established 2026)
├─ Series 2026-1 (£350m) - 4-5 months to establish
├─ Series 2026-2 (£400m) - 6-8 weeks to execute
├─ Series 2026-3 (£350m) - 6-8 weeks to execute
├─ Series 2027-1 (£400m) - 6-8 weeks to execute
└─ [All future issuance through same platform]
```

### Key Features

**Each Series Has:**

- Discrete collateral pool (no cross-collateralization)
- Independent credit enhancement
- Separate waterfall and reserve accounts
- Own rating and investor base

**Shared Infrastructure:**

- Single base prospectus (updated every 3 years)
- Master trust deed and corporate services
- Standing servicer/trustee/cash manager agreements
- Established SPV entity

**Operational Benefits:**

- New series via 20-40 page supplement (vs 200+ page full docs)
- 6-8 week execution (vs 12-16 weeks)
- 60-70% cost reduction per series after Series 1
- Call refinancing built into framework
- Investor familiarity with programme

