## STRUCTURAL FEATURES TO INCORPORATE

### 1. **Collateral Eligibility (Broad Base, Series Flexibility)**

**Programme-Level Maximum Criteria:**

- Loan types: UK residential (owner-occupied, BTL, near-prime)
- LTV: 50-85%
- ICR: Minimum 125% (BTL)
- Geography: England, Wales, Scotland, Northern Ireland
- Loan size: £25k-£750k

**Series-Specific Tightening:**

- Series 2026-1: May target LTV 50-75%, ICR 145% (conservative)
- Series 2026-2: May use full range LTV 50-85%, ICR 125% (capture more volume)
- Flexibility to match market conditions and investor appetite

### 2. **Call Refinancing Mechanism**

**Built into Base Prospectus:**

> “The Issuer may issue notes for the purpose of refinancing any outstanding series, including to exercise optional redemption rights.”

**How It Works:**

- Legacy Polaris 2025-3 call date: Q4 2027
- Issue new Series 2027-4: Use proceeds to exercise call
- Investors can roll from old series to new series
- **Cost: Just new series issuance** (£750k-1.1m vs full refinancing + warehouse bridge)

### 3. **Series Reopening Capability**

**Flexibility Feature:**

- Issue Series 2026-1 at £350m in March
- Market improves by September
- “Reopen” Series 2026-1 for additional £150m
- Same collateral pool (now seasoned), enhanced liquidity
- **Cost: £200-300k (vs £750-1,130k new series)**

### 4. **Private Placement Series**

**Solution for £40m Retained Seconds:**

```
Polaris Master Issuer plc
├─ PUBLIC SERIES (benchmark, listed, marketed)
│   ├─ Series 2026-1: £350m
│   └─ Series 2026-2: £400m
│
└─ PRIVATE SERIES (retained/bespoke, unlisted)
    ├─ Series 2026-A: £40m (retained subordinated)
    ├─ Series 2026-B: £75m (CLO vehicle placement)
    └─ Series 2026-C: £150m (insurance company direct)
```

**Benefits:**

- Same infrastructure (minimal incremental cost)
- Flexible retention/sale strategy
- Balance sheet optimization

